.SH NAME
cap_ptrace_access_check \- Determine whether the current process may access another
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" cap_ptrace_access_check
.BI "(struct task_struct *child "  ","
.BI "unsigned int mode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "child" 12
The process to be accessed
.IP "mode" 12
The mode of attachment.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If we are in the same or an ancestor user_ns and have all the target
task's capabilities, then ptrace access is allowed.
If we have the ptrace capability to the target user_ns, then ptrace
access is allowed.
Else denied.

Determine whether a process may access another, returning 0 if permission
granted, -ve if denied.
